│ that the `Users` list is empty before deleting the object. This indicates that there are   │
│ still users of the `VPValue` object when it is being destroyed.\n\n2. **Analyzing `opt`'s  │
│ Log**: The log shows that the loop vectorizer is attempting to vectorize a loop with       │
│ forced vectorization factors. The `VPValue` object in question is likely part of the VPlan │
│ representation of the loop. The `Users` list of the `VPValue` object contains four         │
│ entries, all of which reference the same `VPValue` object. This suggests a circular        │
│ dependency or a failure to properly clear the `Users` list before destruction.\n\n3.       │
│ **Root Cause Analysis**: The issue likely arises in the `eraseFromParent` method of        │
│ `VPRecipeBase` or in the `removeDefinedValue` method of `VPDef`. These methods are         │
│ responsible for managing the relationships between `VPValue` objects and their users. If   │
│ these methods do not properly update the `Users` list or the `DefinedValues` list, it can  │
│ lead to the assertion failure observed.\n\n4. **Proposed Edit Points**:\n   - **Edit Point │
