│ log the contents of the `Users` list and the `DefinedValues` list before the assertion.    │
│ This will help identify the source of the issue.\n   - **Edit Point 2**: Add validation    │
│ code in `VPRecipeBase::eraseFromParent` (line 237 of `VPlanRecipes.cpp`) to ensure that    │
│ all `VPValue` objects associated with the recipe are properly unlinked from their users    │
│ and definitions before the recipe is erased.\n\n5. **Conclusion**: The proposed changes    │
│ aim to identify and fix the root cause of the issue by ensuring that all relationships     │
│ between `VPValue` objects are properly managed during destruction. This should prevent the │
│ assertion failure and allow the loop vectorizer to complete successfully."})               │
